WEBVTT



00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.048
Leprosy still exists. Every two minutes someone is diagnosed with this disease. In an unjust world, their suffering won't make the headlines. It's hidden in the world's borders.

00:00:09.568 --> 00:00:19.616
Old, poorest places. The physical effects are devastating. But the hardest part is how you are treated. Even if you've been cured, you can be rejected by your family and community.

00:00:19.136 --> 00:00:29.184
isolated, shamed and forgotten. But God sees and so do we. It's time to end leprosy. To learn more, visit leprosymission.org.uk/leprosymission

00:00:28.704 --> 00:00:30.368
UK slash Premier.

00:00:30.944 --> 00:00:40.352
Hello friends, I'm Rick Warren and welcome to Spurgeon's Sermons. This is the official podcast brought to you by Premier and Spurgeon's College.

00:00:40.288 --> 00:00:50.336
You know, the teachings of Charles Spurgeon have had a personal impact on my life in a profound way, and I'm confident they'll do the same for you. So get ready to be challenged.

00:00:49.856 --> 00:00:58.624
be challenged, equipped, and guided by Charles Spurgeon, who is universally regarded as the greatest English preacher in the history of the Church.

00:00:59.584 --> 00:01:01.344
silver sockets.

00:01:01.120 --> 00:01:03.584
Or redemption the foundation.

00:01:03.904 --> 00:01:06.240
Sermon by Charles Spurgeon.

00:01:06.304 --> 00:01:07.552
Part three.

00:01:08.928 --> 00:01:15.648
And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying, When thou takest the sum of the children of Israel after their number,

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:22.528
Then shall they give every man a ransom for his soul unto the Lord, when thou numberest them.

00:01:22.944 --> 00:01:25.664
That there be no plague among them.

00:01:25.664 --> 00:01:27.424
When thou numberest them.

00:01:27.840 --> 00:01:32.992
This they shall give, every one that passeth among them that are numbered.

00:01:32.736 --> 00:01:34.144
Half a shekel,

00:01:34.368 --> 00:01:36.736
After the shekel of the sanctuary,

00:01:36.896 --> 00:01:39.712
A shekel is twenty geras.

00:01:40.512 --> 00:01:43.872
And half shekel shall be the offering of the Lord.

00:01:44.064 --> 00:01:47.712
Every one that passeth among them that are numbered,

00:01:47.424 --> 00:01:50.080
From 20 years old and above,

00:01:50.048 --> 00:01:52.672
Shall give an offering unto the Lord.

00:01:53.088 --> 00:01:55.680
The rich shall not give more,

00:01:55.904 --> 00:01:59.904
And the poor shall not give less than half a shekel.

00:01:59.936 --> 00:02:03.776
When they give an offering unto the Lord, to make an atonement,

00:02:03.744 --> 00:02:05.120
For your souls

00:02:06.016 --> 00:02:10.368
and thou shalt take the atonement money of the children of Israel,

00:02:10.208 --> 00:02:14.656
And shall appoint it for the service of the tabernacle of the congregation.

00:02:15.296 --> 00:02:20.064
That it may be a memorial unto the children of Israel before the Lord.

00:02:19.872 --> 00:02:23.200
To make an atonement for your souls.

00:02:23.840 --> 00:02:26.176
Exodus chapter 30

00:02:26.016 --> 00:02:28.320
11 to 16.

00:02:29.568 --> 00:02:33.472
A beckar for every man, that is half a shekel,

00:02:33.440 --> 00:02:35.712
After the shekel of the sanctuary,

00:02:35.616 --> 00:02:38.208
For everyone that went to be numbered.

00:02:38.240 --> 00:02:40.608
From 20 years old and upward,

00:02:40.704 --> 00:02:45.600
For 603,550 men.

00:02:46.144 --> 00:02:49.376
And of the hundred talents of silver were cast,

00:02:49.120 --> 00:02:51.520
The sockets of the sanctuary.

00:02:51.552 --> 00:02:53.568
And the sockets of the veil.

00:02:53.760 --> 00:02:57.056
And 100 sockets of the 100 talents

00:02:57.056 --> 00:02:59.392
A talent for a socket.

00:03:00.064 --> 00:03:02.560
Exodus chapter 38

00:03:02.560 --> 00:03:05.216
Verses 26 to 27.

00:03:07.040 --> 00:03:10.016
It is not only God's coming to us.

00:03:10.560 --> 00:03:13.280
But God's abiding with us.

00:03:13.280 --> 00:03:16.096
That is upon the same foundation.

00:03:16.672 --> 00:03:19.360
For the tabernacle was, so to speak,

00:03:19.232 --> 00:03:20.736
The house of God.

00:03:21.152 --> 00:03:27.904
The place where God especially dwelt among his people, as he said, "I will dwell in them."

00:03:27.808 --> 00:03:29.632
And walk in them.

00:03:30.304 --> 00:03:34.336
But he never dwelt among them in anything but in a tent,

00:03:34.112 --> 00:03:35.680
That was based

00:03:35.680 --> 00:03:38.592
Upon the silver of the redemption money.

00:03:39.360 --> 00:03:41.184
And you, dear friend?

00:03:41.088 --> 00:03:43.904
If you have ever walked with God,

00:03:44.096 --> 00:03:46.784
Can only maintain your fellowship,

00:03:46.752 --> 00:03:49.760
By resting where you did at first.

00:03:49.696 --> 00:03:51.648
As a poor sinner.

00:03:51.520 --> 00:03:53.632
Redeemed by your saviour.

00:03:54.304 --> 00:03:56.352
They have asked me.

00:03:56.512 --> 00:03:59.648
To rise sometimes to a higher platform.

00:04:00.128 --> 00:04:01.824
and come to God.

00:04:01.664 --> 00:04:03.776
As a sanctified person.

00:04:04.480 --> 00:04:06.336
Yes, but a rock.

00:04:06.560 --> 00:04:11.456
Though it may be lower than the little wooden stage which some build upon it,

00:04:11.552 --> 00:04:13.952
Is safer to stand upon.

00:04:15.360 --> 00:04:17.056
And I do believe.

00:04:16.928 --> 00:04:21.088
That those who walk with God according to their attainments,

00:04:21.280 --> 00:04:23.840
And imaginary perfections

00:04:23.808 --> 00:04:29.664
Have climbed up to a rotten stage which will fall under them before long.

00:04:31.040 --> 00:04:35.008
I know no mood of standing before God today.

00:04:35.360 --> 00:04:38.176
But that which I had at first.

00:04:38.496 --> 00:04:41.856
I am unworthy still in myself.

00:04:42.304 --> 00:04:43.808
But accept it,

00:04:43.584 --> 00:04:44.896
In the beloved

00:04:45.600 --> 00:04:47.712
Guilty in myself.

00:04:47.776 --> 00:04:50.208
And lost and ruined.

00:04:50.592 --> 00:04:54.336
But still received blessed and loved

00:04:54.496 --> 00:04:57.664
Because of the person and work of Christ.

00:04:58.368 --> 00:05:01.728
The Lord cannot dwell with you, my dear friend.

00:05:01.568 --> 00:05:04.352
You will soon have broken fellowship.

00:05:04.128 --> 00:05:05.952
And be in the dark,

00:05:05.920 --> 00:05:08.512
If you attempt to walk with him

00:05:08.256 --> 00:05:10.720
Because you feel sanctified.

00:05:10.624 --> 00:05:14.656
Or because you have been active in his service.

00:05:14.592 --> 00:05:16.768
Or because you know much.

00:05:16.800 --> 00:05:18.080
Or because

00:05:17.824 --> 00:05:20.576
You are an experienced believer.

00:05:21.280 --> 00:05:22.208
No.

00:05:22.144 --> 00:05:23.936
No, no,

00:05:24.352 --> 00:05:29.920
The Lord will only abide with us in that tabernacle whose every board

00:05:29.664 --> 00:05:33.920
Is resting upon the silver foundation of redemption.

00:05:33.952 --> 00:05:36.320
By his own dear son.

00:05:37.632 --> 00:05:39.520
There can, beloved.

00:05:39.520 --> 00:05:43.360
be no sort of communion between God and us.

00:05:43.104 --> 00:05:45.408
Except through the atonement.

00:05:45.824 --> 00:05:47.488
Do you want to pray?

00:05:47.712 --> 00:05:51.616
You cannot speak with God except through Jesus Christ.

00:05:52.064 --> 00:05:53.920
Do you wish to praise?

00:05:54.208 --> 00:05:58.080
You cannot bring the sensor full of smoking incense.

00:05:57.952 --> 00:06:00.064
Except through christ.

00:06:00.736 --> 00:06:04.288
It is only within those foundations of silver

00:06:04.512 --> 00:06:09.312
That you can speak to God or hear him speak comfortably with you.

00:06:10.144 --> 00:06:13.664
Would you hear a voice out of the excellent glory?

00:06:13.984 --> 00:06:19.232
Do you pray that the great Father would speak with you as with his dear children?

00:06:19.456 --> 00:06:21.056
Expect it

00:06:20.864 --> 00:06:22.880
Through Jesus Christ.

00:06:23.200 --> 00:06:24.576
For through him

00:06:24.512 --> 00:06:28.032
We have access by one spirit unto the Father.

00:06:28.448 --> 00:06:31.904
Even unto the Father, though we be children,

00:06:31.808 --> 00:06:33.984
We have not access.

00:06:33.792 --> 00:06:36.128
Except through Jesus.

00:06:36.480 --> 00:06:38.784
The tabernacle of communion

00:06:38.688 --> 00:06:41.824
Even to him that lives nearest to God.

00:06:42.016 --> 00:06:45.504
Must be built upon the redemption price.

00:06:45.888 --> 00:06:47.488
Free grace,

00:06:47.264 --> 00:06:49.024
And dying love.

00:06:49.152 --> 00:06:53.056
Must be the golden bells which ring upon our garments.

00:06:52.896 --> 00:06:55.584
When we go into the holy place,

00:06:55.392 --> 00:06:56.608
To speak,

00:06:56.448 --> 00:06:58.016
With the most high.

00:06:58.720 --> 00:07:02.048
The tabernacle was the place of holy service.

00:07:01.920 --> 00:07:07.936
Where the priests all day long offered sacrifices of one kind and another.

00:07:07.904 --> 00:07:09.632
Unto the most high.

00:07:10.592 --> 00:07:12.032
And you and I?

00:07:11.840 --> 00:07:16.928
Serve God as priests, for he has made us a royal priesthood.

00:07:17.792 --> 00:07:21.664
But how and where can we exercise our priesthood?

00:07:21.952 --> 00:07:23.168
Everywhere.

00:07:22.976 --> 00:07:24.608
As to this world,

00:07:25.088 --> 00:07:26.816
But before God,

00:07:26.912 --> 00:07:30.272
The foundation of the temple wherein we stand

00:07:30.304 --> 00:07:34.048
And the ground of the acceptance of our priesthood.

00:07:33.952 --> 00:07:35.424
Is redemption.

00:07:36.288 --> 00:07:41.344
The priests offered their sacrifice not in groves of people's planting,

00:07:41.472 --> 00:07:43.360
Or on high hills,

00:07:43.232 --> 00:07:45.888
Which were the natural strength of the land.

00:07:46.400 --> 00:07:52.256
But within the space marked out by the silver slabs of atonement money.

00:07:53.120 --> 00:07:55.488
And so must we worship,

00:07:55.456 --> 00:07:58.816
And serve within redemption lines.

00:07:59.488 --> 00:08:00.864
If we come,

00:08:00.704 --> 00:08:03.200
Under the idea of legal merit,

00:08:03.328 --> 00:08:07.424
And suppose that there is a natural goodness in our prayers,

00:08:07.296 --> 00:08:09.056
Or in our praises.

00:08:09.216 --> 00:08:14.016
In our observances of Christian ceremonies or in almsgiving.

00:08:13.792 --> 00:08:15.808
Or in zealous testimony.

00:08:15.680 --> 00:08:17.984
We make a great mistake.

00:08:18.368 --> 00:08:20.864
And we shall never be so accepted.

00:08:21.248 --> 00:08:24.800
We must bring our offerings unto that court.

00:08:24.832 --> 00:08:26.656
Which is fenced about,

00:08:26.464 --> 00:08:29.312
By the foundation most precious.

00:08:29.440 --> 00:08:32.160
Which God has laid of old,

00:08:32.224 --> 00:08:33.760
Even the merit,

00:08:33.408 --> 00:08:35.296
The great light of his dear son.

00:08:36.448 --> 00:08:38.272
We are accepted

00:08:38.176 --> 00:08:39.552
In the beloved.

00:08:39.904 --> 00:08:41.824
And in no other manner.

00:08:42.272 --> 00:08:47.168
We are shut in within the foundation which Christ has laid of old.

00:08:47.488 --> 00:08:51.488
Not with corruptible things as with silver and gold.

00:08:51.968 --> 00:08:53.376
But with his own.

00:08:53.280 --> 00:08:55.232
Most precious blood.

00:08:56.736 --> 00:08:58.656
Thus much, dear brethren,

00:08:58.720 --> 00:09:01.472
Upon one view of this subject.

00:09:01.888 --> 00:09:04.032
May you learn much of God.

00:09:03.904 --> 00:09:05.888
In his relation to man,

00:09:05.632 --> 00:09:08.480
While you meditate thereon at your leisure.

00:09:08.544 --> 00:09:11.264
And are taught of the Holy Spirit.

00:09:12.576 --> 00:09:15.712
I think we may in the second place

00:09:15.648 --> 00:09:18.592
Apply this illustration to Christ

00:09:18.368 --> 00:09:20.608
In his divine person.

00:09:21.216 --> 00:09:22.688
The tabernacle

00:09:22.528 --> 00:09:25.536
was the type of our Lord Jesus Christ.

00:09:25.504 --> 00:09:28.992
For God dwells among men in Christ.

00:09:29.472 --> 00:09:32.096
He tabernacled among us.

00:09:31.904 --> 00:09:35.424
And we beheld his glory, says the Apostle.

00:09:35.936 --> 00:09:39.488
God dwells not in temples made with hands.

00:09:39.808 --> 00:09:42.208
That is to say, of this building.

00:09:43.008 --> 00:09:44.768
But the temple of God

00:09:44.896 --> 00:09:46.880
Is Christ Jesus?

00:09:47.072 --> 00:09:51.488
In whom dwelleth all the fulness of the Godhead bodily?

00:09:52.608 --> 00:09:55.104
Our Lord is thus the tabernacle,

00:09:54.912 --> 00:09:58.304
Which the Lord has pitched, and not man.

00:09:59.040 --> 00:10:02.688
And our first and fundamental idea of him

00:10:02.560 --> 00:10:05.728
must be in his character as Redeemer.

00:10:06.496 --> 00:10:09.984
Our Lord does come to us in other characters.

00:10:10.336 --> 00:10:13.376
And in them all he is right, glorious.

00:10:13.376 --> 00:10:16.256
But unless we receive him as redeemer,

00:10:16.416 --> 00:10:19.392
We have missed the essence of his character.

00:10:19.488 --> 00:10:22.048
The foundation idea of him.

00:10:23.296 --> 00:10:24.704
As the tent,

00:10:24.480 --> 00:10:25.952
In the wilderness.

00:10:25.792 --> 00:10:28.512
Was founded upon the redemption money.

00:10:28.896 --> 00:10:32.320
So our idea and conception of Christ,

00:10:32.160 --> 00:10:34.016
Must first of all.

00:10:34.176 --> 00:10:37.888
Be that he is the propitiation for our sins.

00:10:38.304 --> 00:10:42.336
And I say this, though it may seem unnecessary to say it.

00:10:42.752 --> 00:10:45.472
because Satan is very crafty

00:10:45.600 --> 00:10:48.768
And he leads many from plain truth.

00:10:48.736 --> 00:10:50.464
By subtle means.

00:10:51.008 --> 00:10:52.928
I remember a sister

00:10:52.736 --> 00:10:55.872
Who had been a member of a certain denomination.

00:10:55.840 --> 00:10:59.040
Who was converted to God in this place

00:10:59.296 --> 00:11:02.752
Though she had been a professed Christian for years.

00:11:03.072 --> 00:11:08.128
She said to me, I have hitherto believed only in Christ crucified.

00:11:08.416 --> 00:11:14.560
I worshipped him as about to come in the second advent to reign with his people.

00:11:15.072 --> 00:11:17.472
But I never had a sense of guilt.

00:11:17.952 --> 00:11:21.504
Neither did I go to him as putting away my sin.

00:11:22.176 --> 00:11:23.360
And hence,

00:11:23.232 --> 00:11:25.056
I was not saved.

00:11:26.112 --> 00:11:28.992
When she began to see herself as a sinner,

00:11:29.216 --> 00:11:31.232
She found her need

00:11:31.104 --> 00:11:32.416
Of a redeemer.

00:11:33.312 --> 00:11:34.688
Atonement,

00:11:34.432 --> 00:11:39.616
must enter into our first and chief idea of the Lord Jesus.

00:11:40.384 --> 00:11:42.944
We preach Christ crucified.

00:11:43.552 --> 00:11:45.696
We preach him glorified.

00:11:45.792 --> 00:11:47.808
And delight to do so.

00:11:48.384 --> 00:11:53.024
But still the main point upon which the eye of a sinner must rest.

00:11:53.184 --> 00:11:55.584
If he would have peace with God,

00:11:56.096 --> 00:11:59.296
Must be Christ crucified for sin.

00:12:00.448 --> 00:12:01.824
God forbid!

00:12:01.536 --> 00:12:06.016
That I should glory save in the cross of our Lord Jesus Christ.

00:12:06.656 --> 00:12:12.576
Do, then, my dear hearer, let the very foundation of your faith in Christ,

00:12:12.448 --> 00:12:14.368
Be your view of him.

00:12:14.144 --> 00:12:18.432
as ransoming you from the power of sin and Satan.

00:12:19.104 --> 00:12:22.592
Some say they admire Christ as an example.

00:12:22.784 --> 00:12:24.288
And well they may.

00:12:24.768 --> 00:12:26.848
They can never find a better.

00:12:27.456 --> 00:12:29.184
But Jesus Christ,

00:12:29.184 --> 00:12:32.224
Will never be truly known and followed

00:12:32.224 --> 00:12:35.264
If he be viewed only as an example.

00:12:35.744 --> 00:12:38.592
For he is infinitely more than that.

00:12:39.584 --> 00:12:44.128
Neither can any man carry out the project of being like Christ.

00:12:44.256 --> 00:12:48.512
Unless he first knows him as making atonement for sin.

00:12:49.088 --> 00:12:52.416
And as giving power to overcome sin.

00:12:52.192 --> 00:12:53.504
Through his blood,

00:12:54.720 --> 00:12:58.592
Some writers have looked upon Christ from one point of view

00:12:58.560 --> 00:13:00.288
And some from another.

00:13:00.704 --> 00:13:04.000
And there is no book that is more likely to sell.

00:13:04.160 --> 00:13:06.272
than a life of Christ.

00:13:06.912 --> 00:13:10.272
But the most essential view of him is to be had

00:13:10.144 --> 00:13:11.904
From the cross foot

00:13:12.928 --> 00:13:16.672
No complete life of Christ has been written yet,

00:13:17.152 --> 00:13:20.704
All the lives of Christ that have been yet written,

00:13:20.704 --> 00:13:21.760
Amount

00:13:21.632 --> 00:13:24.224
To about one drop of broth.

00:13:24.736 --> 00:13:26.912
While the four evangelists

00:13:26.976 --> 00:13:28.896
Are as a whole popped.

00:13:29.984 --> 00:13:32.128
The pen of inspiration.

00:13:32.128 --> 00:13:33.632
Has accomplished,

00:13:33.664 --> 00:13:37.792
What all the quills in the world will never be able to do again.

00:13:38.496 --> 00:13:40.896
And there is no need that they should.

00:13:41.824 --> 00:13:45.504
However much we dwell upon the holiness of our Lord,

00:13:45.408 --> 00:13:47.808
We cannot complete his picture.

00:13:47.712 --> 00:13:49.824
Unless we describe him

00:13:49.568 --> 00:13:51.552
As the sinner's ransom.

00:13:52.448 --> 00:13:54.368
When he cometh forth,

00:13:54.208 --> 00:13:56.896
In the vesture dipped in blood,

00:13:56.768 --> 00:13:58.336
Many shun him.

00:13:58.656 --> 00:14:01.888
They cannot bear the atoning sacrifice.

00:14:02.496 --> 00:14:06.240
But he is never in our eyes so matchlessly lovely.

00:14:06.304 --> 00:14:10.144
As when we see him bearing our sins in his own body,

00:14:09.888 --> 00:14:11.232
On the tree.

00:14:11.680 --> 00:14:14.080
And putting away transgression,

00:14:14.144 --> 00:14:16.864
By making himself the substitute.

00:14:16.864 --> 00:14:18.208
For his people.

00:14:19.616 --> 00:14:23.744
Let this then be your basis idea of Christ.

00:14:23.968 --> 00:14:25.824
He has redeemed us.

00:14:25.696 --> 00:14:27.616
From the curse of the law.

00:14:28.512 --> 00:14:31.136
Indeed, in reference to Christ,

00:14:31.360 --> 00:14:33.824
We must regard his redemption.

00:14:33.984 --> 00:14:37.728
As the basis of his triumphs and his glory.

00:14:38.592 --> 00:14:40.864
The sufferings of Christ

00:14:40.832 --> 00:14:43.264
And the glory that shall follow.

00:14:44.224 --> 00:14:47.968
We cannot understand any work that he has performed.

00:14:48.224 --> 00:14:51.936
Unless we understand his vicarious sacrifice.

00:14:52.448 --> 00:14:53.600
Christ

00:14:53.376 --> 00:14:54.528
is a lock.

00:14:54.752 --> 00:14:56.160
Without a key.

00:14:56.640 --> 00:14:58.368
He is a labyrinth.

00:14:58.240 --> 00:14:59.968
Without a clue.

00:15:00.320 --> 00:15:03.296
Until you know him as the redeemer.

00:15:04.288 --> 00:15:07.168
You have spilt the letters on the floor.

00:15:07.136 --> 00:15:10.720
And you cannot make out the character of the wonderful.

00:15:11.040 --> 00:15:12.448
To first

00:15:12.416 --> 00:15:15.104
You have learned to spell the words.

00:15:15.072 --> 00:15:17.568
Atonement by blood

00:15:18.304 --> 00:15:21.472
This is the deepest joy of earth.

00:15:21.536 --> 00:15:24.256
And the grandest song in heaven.

00:15:24.736 --> 00:15:26.912
For thou wast slain

00:15:26.752 --> 00:15:31.072
and hast redeemed us unto God by thy blood.

00:15:32.096 --> 00:15:39.072
Thank you for listening, friends. this podcast was brought to you by Premier in association with Spurgeon's College.

00:15:39.008 --> 00:15:42.656
